title: Upgrade QBits backend
body:
## Type of Change

feature or bug fix or documentation or others: feature
API changed or not: Yes

- unify qbits weight-only linear interface.

- add qbits workspace for accelerate linear calculation.

## Description

detail description 
JIRA ticket: https://jira.devtools.intel.com/browse/NLPTOOLKIU-725

## Expected Behavior & Potential Risk

the expected behavior that triggered by this PR 

- refactored the directory structure  to make it easier for QBits to integrate more features(e.g. sparse) that Jblas may have in the future.

- Added workspace interface  to QBits to accelerate weight-only-linear calculations in QBits with specific compute_types (such as int8).

- Support s8/s4_clip perchannel_quantize weight-only kernels.
-  Support for all compressed weight weight-only kernels with compute_type==fp32 under AVX2.
- Support for any combination of src_type==fp32/bf16 and dst_type==fp32/bf16 under AVX2/AVX512F/AVX512_VNNI/AMX.
- Added a verbose function to QBits to check kernel execute-time, problem size, weight-only configuration, etc.
## How has this PR been tested?

how to reproduce the test (including hardware information)
AVX512F/AVX512_VNNI/AMX_INT8/AMX_BF16 tested on 335T
AVX2 tested on local desktop, Intel Core 10900

any library dependency introduced or removed: No

## Type of Change

Feature add

## Description

New models add:

TODO:

  - https://github.com/intel-innersource/frameworks.ai.lpot.lpot-validation/pull/501
  - https://inteltf-jenk.sh.intel.com/view/nlp-toolkit-validation/job/ITREX-cpp-graph-extension/75/

* The performance of the GLM2 q8_j tested is 8CORE. Thanks @violetch24 
  -  Env:  8260
  -  Conf: q8_j  / block_size 128 & 32
  -  8255c physical machine block_size=128: 80.80ms; block_size=32: 87.84ms
  -  8260 on block_size=128: 91.39ms; block_size=32: 98.42ms (As shown below)

![20a96697-bf0f-47f3-bef0-41949309d5d8](https://github.com/intel/intel-extension-for-transformers/assets/109137058/2ca7c8bf-0933-4b1d-b921-35d626d62da2)

* Issues(Fixed in https://github.com/intel/intel-extension-for-transformers/pull/278):    
  - [x]  Get n_ctx by ctx->model.hparams.n_ctx.
          The rope requires the size of prompts but not the fixed model.haprams.n_ctx. No need to chage.
  - [x] add parameters list bos_token_id / eos_token_id / pad_token_id / sep_token_id to voca.
          These parameters has been added to model.vocab.
  - [x] multi-query-attention(MQA) double check for ChatGLM-2.
          Use n_head_kv instead of multi_query_group_num may cause accuracy issues.

N/A.

Manual and CI tests.
